[Gemini]: The code for `rebuild_auth` confirms the vulnerability. The logic at line 245 only compares the `hostname` of the original and redirected URLs.

```python
if (original_parsed.hostname != redirect_parsed.hostname):
    del headers['Authorization']
```

It does not check if the URL *scheme* has changed (e.g., from `https` to `http`). This means if a request to `https://example.com` redirects to `http://example.com`, the `Authorization` header will be preserved and sent over the unencrypted connection, leaking the credentials. This is a clear instance of CWE-522.

I will now submit this finding.

